table_cells.text: The FG part number is a representation of the wire size and polymer used to produce 1 unit of the FG Pack Size in yards.  For example, G1/0TPO (using tooling pack T1/0) will produce 1 unit at a 15 yard pack size, at a rate of 50 yards per hour.  Consuming 50 pounds of polymer (TPO) and 15 yards of G1/0 wire for each unit produced.
